SEC. 2. Section 9 of Republic Act No. 7978 is hereby amended to read as follows:

"SEC. 9. In consideration of the franchise and rights herein granted, the grantee shall pay to the national treasury a franchise tax equal to twenty-five percent (25%) of its gross earnings, which is equivalent to the commissions/fees earned by the grantee out of total wager funds, allotted as follows:

"(a) Three percent (3%) to the national government;

"(b) Five percent (5%) to the City of Kalookan, or if the racetrack is located elsewhere, then to such city or municipality where it is located;

"(c) Five percent (5%) to the public health workers under the Magna Carta for Public Health Workers and three percent (3%) to the cardiovascular program of the Department of Health;

"(d) Five percent (5%) to the Philippine Anti-Tuberculosis Society;

"(e) Two percent (2%) to the White Cross; and

"(f) Two percent (2%) to the Water For Life program of the Department of Health.
